"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-emma-finucane-bronze-medal-b1175543.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  The keirin, they said, was the chink in the armour ofTeam GB's new sprint queen and so it proved forEmma Finucane.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 303, \"end\": 305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7941460979577891, \"rank\": 0.2592141444643745, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Setting out with the dream of emulating Chris Hoy and Jason Kenny as a triple sprint gold medallist at a singleOlympic Games, Hoy had tipped her to pull off the triumvirate.\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}, {\"begin\": 415, \"end\": 426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jason Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Already she had one gold to her name - in the team sprint - and had been sleeping with it under her pillow, greeting her roommate Katy Marchant with the words \\\"morning Olympic gold medallist\\\" first thing.\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 666, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katy Marchant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this was always the weakest of the 21-year-old's trio of events with her relative lack of experience and tactical acumen in track cycling's high-speed game of chess.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 911, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And she was upstaged by the world champion Ellesse Andrews, of New Zealand, and the Netherlands Hetty van de Wouw to finish with a bronze.\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 1051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 956, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellesse_Andrews\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ellesse Andrews\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellesse_Andrews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellesse_Andrews\"}, {\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6370134483999781, \"rank\": 0.569821601276309, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hetty_van_de_Wouw\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hetty van de Wouw\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hetty_van_de_Wouw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hetty_van_de_Wouw\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a second Olympic medal to her name in her first Games at the age of 21, she said, \\\"that bronze literally feels like a gold\\\".\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is the realistic ambition of another medal - even a second gold to sneak under her pillow - come Sunday's track finale in the individual sprint where she is the world champion and will be among the favourites.\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Reset your wellbeing for the year ahead  It had not been plain sailing throughout the rounds of the keirin only sneaking into the final by finishing third and in the final qualification spot in the semi-finals.\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1532, \"end\": 1548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 1703, \"end\": 1709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3375369329894318e-59, \"text\": \"keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a crowd that seemed remarkably British in its support, including her parents Rory and Susie who had driven to Paris in a hired campervan and wore navy blue Team Finucane T-shirts, it felt like home from home.\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1897, \"end\": 1901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_Williams\", \"score\": 0.8605105044278003, \"rank\": 0.16210086321385317, \"text\": \"Rory\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Su_Yung\", \"score\": 0.9976578497630295, \"rank\": 0.002347648783007295, \"text\": \"Susie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Su_Yung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Su_Yung\"}, {\"begin\": 1930, \"end\": 1935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.431554744393256e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And she went into the event brimming with confidence from one gold already in the team sprint.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2124, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Come the final of the keirin, an athlete labelled \\\"the superstar\\\" of the British team by none other than Hoy calmly put herself at the back of the pack.\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2198, \"end\": 2205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9929874269791833, \"rank\": 0.006985651126160404, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just before the derny bike pulled off, Finucane made her move up the pack and tried to raise the pace alongside Andrews with two laps to go.\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2419, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But she could never find a way past the Kiwi and was also eclipsed late on by van de Wouw.\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\", \"score\": 0.9989030386338343, \"rank\": 0.001056142721686867, \"text\": \"Kiwi\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_league_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2506, \"end\": 2510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wouw\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wouw\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wouw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wouw\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finucane's teammate Katy Marchant was fourth.\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katy Marchant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think I went a lap too early,\\\" she concluded afterwards.\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2618, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I gave everything I could on the track today and that bronze medal means everything to me after the team sprint on Monday with the girls.\", \"from\": 2619, \"to\": 2757, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was so, so hard but it was worth it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Marchant, there was no individual medal to compare with Finucane at the start of each day and she admitted afterwards, \\\"Fourth place is the worst place to finish.\\\"\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jack Carlin looked to have been knocked out by Kaiya Ota in a surprise result in the individual sprint after losing the first of three heats against the Japanese rider.\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 3137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2969, \"end\": 2973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"score\": 0.8332410976717071, \"rank\": 0.20013268979653207, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\"}, {\"begin\": 2974, \"end\": 2980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999988583788004, \"rank\": 1.1416223702605196e-06, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}, {\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"score\": 0.9999998796033723, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaiya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\"}, {\"begin\": 3022, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Military_and_Technical_Training_Center_of_the_Air_Force\", \"score\": 0.9999964236708652, \"rank\": 1.5318759608055897e-06, \"text\": \"Ota\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Military_and_Technical_Training_Center_of_the_Air_Force\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Military_and_Technical_Training_Center_of_the_Air_Force\"}, {\"begin\": 3122, \"end\": 3130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9473272086612511, \"rank\": 0.04259299659042989, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Ota was belatedly relegated for veering off his line in heat two to set up a decider, which Carlin won by just half a wheel to put him into Thursday's semi-finals.\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3235, \"end\": 3241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999988583788004, \"rank\": 1.1416223702605196e-06, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hamish Turnbull, also of Britain, won his opening heat against Jeffrey Hoogland but lacked the pace to go with him in the next two.\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3308, \"end\": 3323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Turnbull\", \"score\": 0.9999996070519818, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hamish Turnbull\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Turnbull\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Turnbull\"}, {\"begin\": 3333, \"end\": 3340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9738457165074328, \"rank\": 0.026856697131914426, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3371, \"end\": 3387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Hoogland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeffrey Hoogland\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Hoogland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Hoogland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Ethan Hayter, part of the silver medal-winning team in the pursuit the preceding night,  had to make do with eighth overall in the omnium.\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3445, \"end\": 3457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ethan Hayter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 4463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3645, \"end\": 3654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9999996993642978, \"rank\": 2.3344017525140878e-07, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 3745, \"end\": 3754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.9999996993642978, \"rank\": 2.3344017525140878e-07, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.or